### Lesson Recap

In this lesson, you got some practice with understanding how functions and the logic that goes into functions is created in R.  

1. Control flow and conditional statements.  The basic syntax of if statements in R looks like:
```
if (condition1){
      perform if condition1 met
} else if (condition2){
      perform if condition2 met
} else {
     perform if none of the conditions are met
}
```
2. Loops.  The general structure looks like the following:
```
for (val in array){
    perform for all elements in array
}
```
3. Functions.  The general structure follows:
```
function.name = function(inputs){
     do something with inputs
     return(results)
}
```

There is a lot more to know about writing your own functions, but the goal of this lesson is to give you just a glimpse.  In most cases, you can perform many operations in R using functions that have already been written!
